Instruction: Carefully open or view through the available inspection access on the power supply module and perform a detailed visual inspection of the internal wiring from the battery contacts to the LED/resistor branch and to the outgoing cables, as well as any internal connectors or PCB traces. Look for obvious opens, broken or unsoldered wires, missing jumpers, loose internal plug-in connectors, or signs that the battery terminals are not actually connected to the rest of the circuit.
