TYPE: Test,
TARGET: Power supply module output cables and downstream series path,
DESCRIPTION: With the now-good battery installed in the power supply module and all modules connected as in normal operation, measure the voltage directly on the two PSU output terminals/cables. Then move stepwise down the series chain: measure the voltage between the two terminals at the input of control module 1, then at its output, and similarly at the input and output of each subsequent control module up to the load module. Record at which point (between which two modules) the measured voltage first drops from approximately 12 V to 0 V.,
RESULT: The PSU output shows ~12 V across its (+) and (−) cables, and this ~12 V is present across the input and output of control modules 1 and 2. The first point where the measured voltage between the module terminals drops from ~12 V to ~0 V is across control module 3 (between its input (+)/input (−) and especially between its output (+)/output (−)), and it remains ~0 V for all subsequent modules and at the load.
