Instruction: With the system powered and all modules connected, focus on control module 3. First, verify with a meter that ~12 V is present between its input (+) and input (−) terminals. Then, with the module switch in the ON position, measure (a) the voltage across the switch terminals, (b) the voltage from the input (+) to the output (+), and from input (−) to output (−), and (c) the voltage across the red indicator LED+series resistor inside the module. This will determine whether CM3 is internally open, shorted, or miswired and whether its indicator branch is receiving 12 V.
